tech.mcprison.prison.internal.inventory

Interface ShapedRecipe

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Recipe

    public interface ShapedRecipe
extends Recipe
    Represents a shaped crafting recipe (a recipe that must be of a specific shape to be completed). An example of this is the crafting recipe for a Bow.

      • setIngredient

        ShapedRecipe setIngredient(char key,
                           BlockType ingredient)
        Maps an ingredient to a character.

        In the shape() method, you set the shape using different characters for different items. This method assigns a character to an ingredient (item). See the documentation for shape() for more information.

        Parameters:
        key - the character to assign the ingredient to
        ingredient - the ingredient
        Returns:
        this instance to allow chain calls

      • shape

        ShapedRecipe shape(java.lang.String... shape)
        Sets the shape of this recipe

        Example: If you assign letter D to Diamond and S to Stick, the following recipe would give you a Diamond Pickaxe: "DDD", "-S-", "-S-"

        Parameters:
        shape - the new shape of this recipe
        Returns:
        this instance to allow chain calls
